# Security Configuration Checklist
// SSH key-based authentication
// Passwork login disabled
// Non-root admin user (sudo only)
// Allow SSH only from workstation address
// Routine security updates dont automatically
// AppArmor and SELinux configured
// Fail2ban configured
// Security baseline verification script created

Threat model
| Threat                      | Risk                | Mitigation                   |
| --------------------------- | ------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Brute force SSH             | Unauthorized access | Disable passwords + fail2ban |
| Unauthorized network access | System compromise   | Firewall + host-only network |
| Privilege escalation        | System takeover     | Principle of least privilege |
